===========================================================
🌐 NETWORK CONFIGURATION & TROUBLESHOOTING
===========================================================

ip a                                → Show all network interfaces and IP addresses
ip addr show                         → Alternative to view interface details
ifconfig                             → Display network interfaces (legacy)
ip link show                          → Show link-layer info for interfaces
ip route                              → Show routing table
route -n                               → Show numeric routing table

ping <host>                           → Test connectivity to a host
traceroute <host>                     → Trace path packets take to a host
mtr <host>                            → Continuous network trace and stats

netstat -tuln                          → Show listening ports and connections
ss -tuln                               → Modern alternative to netstat
lsof -i                                → List processes using network sockets
ss -s                                  → Show summary of socket statistics

curl <url>                             → Get data from a URL
curl -I <url>                          → Get HTTP headers from a URL
wget <url>                             → Download files from a URL

hostname                               → Show current hostname
hostname -I                             → Display all assigned IP addresses

nmcli dev show                          → Show NetworkManager device details
nmcli con show                          → List all network connections

ethtool <interface>                     → Show Ethernet interface details
iwconfig                               → Show wireless interface configuration
iwlist <interface> scan                 → Scan available Wi-Fi networks

arp -a                                  → Show ARP cache (IP ↔ MAC mappings)
nmap -sn <network/mask>                 → Ping scan to discover live hosts
netdiscover -r <network/mask>           → Discover devices on local network

scp <file> user@host:/path              → Secure copy files to remote host
ssh <user>@<host>                        → Connect to remote host via SSH
rsync -avz <source> <user>@<host>:/dest → Sync files to remote host
